India TRansport System
India has a vast and diverse transporation
1) Road transport:- India has  one of the largest road networks in the world with a  national highway and rural roads.
2) Rail trasport:- India Railways is is one of the largest rail networks  globally connecting  even  remote areas.
3) Air Transport:- India has  numerous domestic and international  airports.major cities have well  connected air travel services.
Public Transport:- Cities  have public transport system like buses and metors,trains.
5) Automobiles:- The Automobiles industry is significant with  a growing number  of vechicles onthe road including cars,motor cycles and scooter.
challenges:- The India Transport systemfaces challengessuchas traffic  congestion , inadequate infrastructure insome areas, and concerns about safty and  environmental
sustainability.
